UML:TaggedValue.value: Dit instrument wordt gebruikt voor patienten met systemische vasculitis
voor het gebruik van het instrument hoeven geen licenties te worden afgesloten

Luqmani RA, Bacon PA, Moots RJ, Janssen BA, Pall A, Emery P, et al. Birmingham Vasculitis Activity Score (BVAS) in systemic necrotizing vasculitis. QJM 1994;87:671–8. Oliver Flossmann, Paul Bacon, Kirsten de Groot, David Jayne, Niels Rasmussen, Philip Seo, Kerstin Westman, Raashid Luqmani; Development of comprehensive disease assessment in systemic vasculitis; Ann Rheum Dis 2007;66:283–292. doi: 10.1136/ard.2005.051078

http://rarediseasesnetwork.epi.usf.edu/vcrc/documents/BVAS%202003.pdf

Als excel (inclusief berekening scores)te downloaden via http://www.ndorms.ox.ac.uk/profiles.php?profile=rluqmani

Luqmani et al (1994) publiceerden de eerste versie van de BVAS en het instrument is gevalideerd in diverse patientgroepen. Sindsien is de BVAS op een aantal punten aangepast en gevalideerd in diverse Europese vasculitis studies. Er zijn hierbij items vervangen, toegevoegd en item scores veranderd. Naast de initiele BVAS bestaat ook de BVAS/WG( Birmingham Vasculitis Activity Score for Wegener’s granulomatosis, de BVAS2 waarin het ook mogelijk werd om bestaande vasculitis te scoren in een separate kolom. Dit zorgde voor verwarring en bij de nieuwste versie ,de BVAS 2003, is onder andere deze 2e kolom vervangen door ‘persistent only disease’ optie waarbij de zorgverlener kan aangeven dat alle positieve items behoren bij een active ziekte in plaats van een bestaande ziekte/persistent disease. (Flossmann 2007)
De uitkomst van de score wordt gebruikt bij het bepalen van de (medicamenteuze) behandeling van de patient.
De Birmingham Vasculitis Assessment Score (BVAS-2003) wordt gebruikt om de mate van actieve vasculitis aan te geven en wordt frequent gebruikt bij Wegener’s granulomatose.

Omdat het instrument in de loop der jaren is gewijzigd in aantal items en bijbehorende score is het belangrijk om alle aangevinkte items zodanig herkenbaar op te slaan zodat achteraf precies de gescorde vraag is te herleiden. Hiermee zijn de verzamelde gegevens vervolgens ook bruikbaar voor onderzoek waarin eerdere versies van de BVAS zijn gebruikt. Het is af te raden om enkel de som- of totaalscore op te slaan.
Deze DCM mag door iedereen gebruikt worden

Parelsnoer als uitvoerder besteedt de grootst mogelijke zorg aan de betrouwbaarheid en actualiteit van de gegevens in deze DCM. Onjuistheden en onvolledigheden kunnen echter voorkomen. Parelsnoer is niet aansprakelijk voor schade als gevolg van onjuistheden of onvolledigheden in de aangeboden informatie, noch voor schade die het gevolg is van problemen veroorzaakt door, of inherent aan het verspreiden van informatie via het internet, zoals storingen of onderbrekingen van of fouten of vertraging in het verstrekken van informatie of diensten door Parelsnoer of door U aan Parelsnoer via een website van Parelsnoer of via e-mail, of anderszins langs elektronische weg. Tevens aanvaardt Parelsnoer geen aansprakelijkheid voor eventuele schade die geleden wordt als gevolg van het gebruik van gegevens, adviezen of ideeën verstrekt door of namens parelsnoer via deze DCM, Detailed Clinical Model. Parelsnoer aanvaardt geen verantwoordelijkheid voor de inhoud van informatie in deze DCM waarnaar of waarvan met een hyperlink of anderszins wordt verwezen. In geval van tegenstrijdigheden in de genoemde DCM documenten en bestanden geeft de meest recente en hoogste versie van de vermelde volgorde in de revisies de prioriteit van de desbetreffende documenten weer. Indien informatie die in de elektronische versie van deze DCM is opgenomen ook schriftelijk wordt verstrekt, zal in geval van tekstverschillen de schriftelijke versie bepalend zijn. Dit geldt indien de versieaanduiding en datering van beiden gelijk is. Een definitieve versie heeft prioriteit echter boven een conceptversie. Een gereviseerde versie heeft prioriteit boven een eerdere versie.

UML:Constraint.name: RenalScore is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 6 or 12

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicationPersistentDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 6 else 12 endif in let wHypertension: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 4 endif in let wProteinuria: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 4 endif in let wHaematuria: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 6 endif in let wCreatinin: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 2 endif in let wCreatininRiseOrClearance: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 0 else 6 endif in
let total: Integer = Hypertension.value*wHypertension + ProteinuriaOver1plus.value*wProteinuria + HaematuriaOver10rbcPerHpf.value*wHaematuria + Creatinine.value*wCreatinin + RiseInCreatinineOver30percentOrCreatinineClearanceFallOver25percent.value*wCreatininRiseOrClearance in
if (total < maxValue) then RenalScore = total else RenalScore = maxValue
Sudden loss of vision requiring ophthalmological assessment
Tenderness or pain over paranasal sinuses with pathologic imaging (CT, MR, x-ray, ultrasound)
Severe headache with neck stiffness ascribed to inflammatory meningitis after excluding infection/bleeding

Cerebrovascular accident resulting in focal neurological signs such as paresis, weakness, etc. A stroke due to other causes (eg atherosclerosis) should be considered & appropriate neurological advice is recommended
Total BVAS score, which is the sum of the group scores
Documented oral/axillary temperature elevation. Rectal temps are 0.5 degrees C higher
Pleural pain and/or friction rub on clinical assessment or new onset of radiologically confirmed pleural effusion. Other causes (e.g. infection, malignancy) should be excluded

Protrusion of the eyeball due to significant amounts of inflammatory in the orbit; if unilateral, there should be a difference of 2 mm between one eye and the other. This may be associated with diplopia due to infiltration of extra-ocular muscles. Developing myopia (measured on best visual acuity, see later) can also be a manifestation of proptosis
Significant valve abnormalities in the aortic mitral or pulmonary valves detected clinically or echocardiographically
Findings, related to the nervous system

UML:Constraint.name: NervousScore is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 6 or 9

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicatorPersistentDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 6 else 9 endif in let wHeadache: Integer = 1 in let wMeningitis: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 3 endif in let wOrganicConfusion: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 3 endif in let wSeizures: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 9 endif in let wStroke: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 9 endif in let wCordLesion: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 9 endif in let wCranialNervePalsy: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 6 endif in let wSensoryPeripheralNeuropathy: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 6 endif in let wMotorMononeuritisMultiplex: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 9 endif in
let total: Integer = Headache.value*wHeadache + Meningitis.value*wMeningitis + OrganicConfusion.value*wOrganicConfusion + Seizures.value*wSeizures + Stroke.value*wStroke + CordLesion.value*wCordLesion + CranialNervePalsy.value*wCranialNervePalsy + SensoryPeripheralNeuropathy.value*wSensoryPeripheralNeuropathy + MotorMononeuritisMultiplex.value*wMotorMononeuritisMultiplex in
if (total < maxValue) then NervousScore.value = total else NervousScore = maxValue endif
Indicates whether a finding is present or not
Transverse myelitis with lower extremity weakness or sensory loss (usually with a detectable sensory level) with loss of sphincter control (rectal & urinary bladder).
Impaired orientation, memory or other intellectual function in the absence of metabolic, psychiatric, pharmacological or toxic causes.
Group score for the cardiovasular system
Area of tissue necrosis or splinter haemorrhages
Diastolic BP>95, accelerated or not, with or without retinal changes.
Bloody, mucopurulent, nasal secretion, light or dark brown crusts frequently obstructing the nose, nasal ulcers and/or granulomatous lesions observed by rhinoscopy
Group score for the ears, the nose and the throat
At least 2kg loss of body weight (not fluid) having occurred since last assessment or in the 4 weeks not as a consequence of dieting
Significant impairment of cardiac function due to poor ventricular wall motion confirmed on echocardiography

UML:Constraint.name: Abdominal score is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 4 or 9

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicatorPersistenDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 4 else 9 endif in let wPeritonitis: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 9 endif in let wBloodyDiarrhoea: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 9 endif in let wIschaemicAbdominalPain: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 6 endif in let total: Integer = Peritonitis.value + BloodyDiarrhoea.value + IschaemicAbdominalPain.value in
if (total < maxValue) then (AbdominalScore.value = total) else AbdominalScore.value = maxValue endif
Facial nerve palsy, recurrent nerve palsy, oculomotor nerve palsy etc. excluding sensorineural hearing loss and ophthalmic symptoms due to inflammation

Conjunctivitis: Inflammation of the conjuctivae (exclude infectious causes and excluding uveitis as cause of red eye, also exclude conjunctivitis sicca which should not be scored as this is not a feature of active vasculitis); (specialist opinion not usually required) Blepharitis: Inflammation of eyelids. Exclude other causes (trauma, infection). Usually no specialist opinion is required Keratitis: Inflammation of central or peripheral cornea as evaluated by specialist

UML:Constraint.name: CutaneousScore is the sum of all scores, but less than or equal to 3 or 6

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv: let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicatorPersistentDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if isPersistent then 3 else 6 endif in let wInfarct: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 2 endif in let wPurpura: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 2 endif in let wUlcer: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 4 endif in let wGangrene: Integer = if isPersistent then 2 else 6 endif in let wOther: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 2 endif in
if Infarct.value*wInfarct + Purpura.value*wPurpura + Ulcer.value*wUlcer + Gangrene.value*wGangrene + OtherSkinVasculitis.value*wOther < maxValue then CutaneousScore.value =Infarct.value*wInfarct + Purpura.value*wPurpura + Ulcer.value*wUlcer + Gangrene.value*wGangrene + OtherSkinVasculitis.value*wOther else CutaneousScore.value = maxValue
Heart failure by history or clinical examination
Pericardial pain &/or friction rub on clinical assessment
Findings, related to the cardiovascular system

UML:Constraint.name: CardiovascularScore is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 3 or 6

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicatorPersistentDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if (isPersisten) then 3 else 6 endif in let wLossOfPulses: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 4 endif in let wValvularHeartDisease: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 4 endif in let wPericarditis: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 3 endif in let wIschaemicCardiacPain: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 4 endif in let wCardiomyopathy: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 6 endif in let wCongestiveCardiacFailure: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 6 endif in let total: Integer = LossOfPulses.value*wLossOfPulses + ValvularHeartDisease.value*wValvularHeartDisease + Pericarditis.value*wPericarditis + IschaemicCardiacPain.value*wIschaemicCardiacPain + Cardiomyopathy.value*wCardiomyopathy + CongestiveCardiacFailure.value*wCongestiveCardiacFailure in
if total < maxValue then (CardiovascularScore.value = total) else CardiovascularScore.value = maxValue endif
Pain in the joints or joint inflammation
Open sore in a skin surface
Group score for the mucous membranes and the eyes
Inflammation of the sclerae (specialist opinion usually required). Can be heralded by photophobia
Findings, related to the mucous membranes or the eyes

UML:Constraint.name: MucousScore is the sum of all scores, but less than or equal to 3 or 6

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicatorPersistentDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if isPersistent then 3 else 6 endif in let wMouthUlcers: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 2 endif in let wGenitalUlcers: Integer = 1 in let wAdnexalInflammation: Integer = if isPersistent then 2 else 4 endif in let wSignificantProptosis: Integer = if isPersisten then 2 else 4 endif in let wScleritisOrEpiscleritis: Integer = if isPersisten then 1 else 2 endif in let wConjunctivitisOrBlepharitisOrKeratitis: Integer = 1 in let wBlurredVision: Integer = if isPersistent then 2 else 3 endif in let wSuddenVisualLoss: Integer = if isPersistent then 0 else 6 endif in let wUveitis: Integer = if isPersistent then 2 else 6 endif in let wRetinalChanges: Integer = if isPersistent then 2 else 6 endif in let total: Integer = MouthUlcers.value*wMouthUlcers + GenitalUlcers.value*wGenitalUlcers + AdnexalInflammation.value*wAdnexalInflammation + SignificantProptosis.value*wSignificantProptosis + ScleritisOrEpiscleritis.value*wScleritisOrEpiscleritis + ConjunctivitisOrBlepharitisOrKeratitis.value*wConjunctivitisOrBlepharitisOrKeratitis + BlurredVision.value*wBlurredVision + SuddenVisualLoss.value*wVisualLoss + Uveitis.value*wUveitis + RetinalChanges.value*wRetinalChanges in
if total < maxValue then MucousScore.value = total else MucousScore.value = maxValue endif
Het invullen van alle onderdelen van de score is verplicht. Ontbreekt er een onderdeel, dan wordt dit geinterpreteerd als 'binnen dit onderdeel is geen afwijking geconstateerd'
Livedo reticularis, subcutaneous nodules, erythema nodosum, etc.
Stridor and hoarseness due to inflammation and narrowing of the subglottic area observed by laryngoscopy
Group score for kidney related findings
>1+ on urinalysis; >0.2g/24 hours Infection should be excluded.
Paroxysmal electrical discharges in the brain & producing characteristic physical changes including tonic & clonic movements & certain behavioural changes.
Of recent onset; inflammatory bowel disease and infectious causes excluded
Hearing loss due to middle ear involvement confirmed by otoscopy and/or tuning fork examination and/or audiometry
Simultaneous neuritis of many peripheral nerves, only scored if motor involvement. Other causes should be excluded (diabetes, sarcoidosis, carcinoma, amyloidosis).
Hearing loss due to auditory nerve or cochlear damage confirmed by audiometry
This item is only to be filled in on the first visit. If the score is done in another visit, 'follow-up' is selected and nothing is scored for this item

UML:Constraint.name: GeneralScore is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 3

UML:TaggedValue.value: inv: let maxValue: Integer = if (owner.IndicatorPersistentDiseaseOnly.value) then 2 else 3 endif in if (Myalgia.value + ArthralgiaOrArthritis.value + FeverOver38C.value*2 + WeightLoss.value*2 < maxValue) then GeneralScore.value = Myalgia.value + ArthralgiaOrArthritis.value + FeverOver38C.value*2 + WeightLoss.value*2 else GeneralScore.value = maxValue
Dyspnoea which is sufficiently severe as to require artificial ventilation
Major pulmonary bleeding, with shifting pulmonary infiltrates; other causes of bleeding should be excluded if possible
10 or more RBC per hpf ( high power field ), excluding urinary infection and urinary lithiasis (stone)
Findings, related to the ears, the nose or the throat

UML:Constraint.name: ENTscore is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 3 or 6

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = Owner.IndicatorPersistentDiseaseOnly.value in let wBloodyNasalDischargeOrCrustsOrUlcersOrGranulomata: Integer = if isPersistent then 3 else 6 endif in let wParanasalSinusInvolvement: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 2 endif in let wSubglotticStenosis: Integer = if isPersistent then 3 else 6 endif in let wConductiveDeafness: Integer = if isPersistent then 1 else 3 endif in let wSensorineuralHearingLoss: Integer = if isPersistent then 2 else 6 endif in let total: Integer = BloodyNasalDischargeOrCrustsOrUlcersOrGranulomata.value*wBloodyNasalDischargeOrCrustsOrUlcersOrGranulomata + ParanasalSinusInvolvement.value*wParanasalSinusInvolvement + SubglotticStenosis.value*wSubglotticStenosis + ConductiveDeafness.value*wConductiveDeafness + SensorineuralHearingLoss.value*wSensorineuralHearingLoss in
if total < maxValue then ENTscore.value = total else ENTscore.value = maxValue
Acute abdominal pain with peritonism/peritonitis due to perforation/infarction of small bowel, appendix or gallbladder etc., or acute pancreatitis confirmed by radiology/surgery/elevated amylase
Salivary (diffuse, tender swelling unrelated to meals) or lacrimal gland inflammation. Exclude other causes (infection). Specialist opinion preferably required
Petechiae (small red spots), palpable purpura, or ecchymoses (large plaques) in skin or oozing (in the absence of trauma) in the mucous membranes.

Retinal vasculitis: Retinal vessel sheathing on examination by specialist or confirmed by retinal fluoroscein angiography Retinal vessel thrombosis: Arterial or venous retinal blood vessel occlusion Retinal exudates: Any area of soft retinal exudates (exclude hard exudates) seen on ophthalmoscopic examination Retinal haemorrhages: Any area of retinal haemorrhage seen on ophthalmoscopic examination
This value indicates whether all documented symptoms are caused by persisting, dormant disease. Meaning they are not symptoms of new, aggravated disease
Altered measurement of best visual acuity from previous or baseline, requiring specialist opinion for further evaluation
Severe abdominal pain with typical features of ischaemia confirmed by imaging or at surgery, with typical appearances of aneursyms or abnormal vasculature characteristic of vasculitis.
Inflammation of the uvea (iris, ciliary body, choroid) confirmed by ophthalmologist
Ulcers localised in the genitalia or perineum, excluding infections
Significant deterioration in renal function attributable to active vasculitis.
8e. Rise in creatinine > 30% or creatinine clearance fall > 25%
Sensory neuropathy resulting in glove &/or stocking distribution of sensory loss. Other causes should be excluded (e.g. idiopathic, metabolic, vitamin deficiencies, infectious, toxic, hereditary).
Typical clinical history of cardiac pain leading to myocardial infarction or angina. Consider the possibility of more common causes (eg atherosclerosis)
Group score for the abdominal findings
Detected by CXR or CT scan. Other causes (infection) should be excluded

UML:Constraint.name: Chest score is the sum of the scores, but less than or equal to 3 or 6

UML:TaggedValue.value:
inv:
let isPersistent: Boolean = owner.IndicatorPersistenDiseaseOnly.value in let maxValue: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 3 else 6 endif in let wWheeze: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 1 else 2 endif in let wNodulesOrCavities: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 0 else 3 endif in let wPleuralEffusionOrPleurisy: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 4 endif in let wInfiltrate: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 4 endif in let wEndobronchialInvolvement: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 2 else 4 endif in let wMassiveHaemoptysisOrAlveolarHaemorr: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 4 else 6 endif in let wRespiratoryFailure: Integer = if (isPersistent) then 4 else 6 endif in let total: Integer = Wheeze.value*wWheeze + NodulesOrCavities.value*wNodulesOrCavities + PleuralEffusionOrPleurisy.value*wPleuralEffusionOrPleurisy + Infiltrate.value*wInfiltrate + EndobronchialInvolvement.value*wEndobronchialInvolvement + MassiveHaemoptysisOrAlveolarHaemorr.value*wMassiveHaemoptysisOrAlveolarHaemorr + RespiratoryFailure.value*wRespiratoryFailure in
if ( total<maxValue) then (ChestScore.value = total) else ChestScore.value = maxValue endif
Group score for the nervous system
Loss of pulses in any vessel detected clinically; this may include loss of pulses leading to threatened loss of limb

Endobronchial pseudotumor or ulcerative lesions. Other causes such as infection or malignancy should be excluded. NB: smooth stenotic lesions to be included in VDI; subglottic lesions to be recorded in the ENT section.
Aphthous stomatitis, deep ulcers and/or “strawberry” gingival hyperplasia, excluding lupus erythematosus, and infection
